{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review and refund overcharged UK Student and Child Student visa fees",
        "additional_details": "We are calling on the Government to review which students were affected, notify them all and make the refund process clear and accessible. Due to a drafting error in law, international students who paid UK Student visa fees from Autumn 2023 onwards were overcharged - by \u00a3127 or \u00a3161. This was confirmed by the House of Lords Secondary Legislation Scrutiny Committee. The Home Office's own refunds policy allows claims within 5 years, yet affected students have never been officially notified.",
        "background": "International students who paid UK Student visa fees from Autumn 2023 onwards were overcharged \u00a3127-\u00a3161, confirmed by a House of Lords Committee. The Home Office's own refunds policy allows claims within 5 years but affected students have never been officially notified.",
